the lives of holy women in other traditions, it also brings to light the largely unwritten history of early-modern Jewish women. To this day, her transgressive behavior, a challenge to traditional Jewish views of gender and sexuality, continues to inspire debate and, sometimes, censorship within the Jewish community.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWomen rabbisvBiography. 0aWomen rabbisxBiography. 0aZaddikotvBiography. 0aZaddikotxBiography. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  abiography.  acharismatic leader.  acommunity.  aconversion.  adiaspora.  aeurope.  afeminism.  agender roles.  agender studies.  agender.  ahasidic.  ahasidism.  ahistorical women.  aholy women.  aimmigration.  ajewish feminism.  ajewish history.  ajewish mysticism.  ajewish women.  ajewish.  ajudaica.  ajudaism.  akabbalah.  aludmir.  amaiden of ludmir.  amaiden.  amarriage.  amartyr.  amigration.  amodernity.  amysticism.  anonfiction.  aottoman empire.  apalestine.  aprophecy.  arebbe.  areligion.  areligious leaders.  areligious women.  arussia.  asexuality.  avisions.  awomen and religion.  awomens issues.  ayiddishkeit.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092797140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520927971423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520927971/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles